{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"947ed644-6338-488b-9233-47cb7dce737f","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth` flag with `None`, `Individual` (Identity/JWT), `IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or frameworks like NestJS/Fastify\n- Auth: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, local), express-jwt, Auth0 SDK\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` for JWT, or `authlib` for OAuth2\n- Auth: OAuth2 password/bearer, API keys, session-based\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- `spring-boot-starter-web` + `spring-boot-starter-security`\n- Auth: JWT, OAuth2 Resource Server, Basic Auth, LDAP\n\nFor example, to scaffold a .NET Web API with JWT auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\nWhich stack are you targeting? I can help scaffold the project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e10afc82-6c19-4dca-aa26-e02c5425e80f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"4818:335471:E7AD3:115F89:69EABD76"},"id":"8e3ea44c-b1bb-43e9-8407-cb336324f9e4","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:46:55.962Z","parentId":"205566b4-cc3f-4495-b1c9-1a1402fa75bb"}
